race.description: GD & SL O'Sullivan Builders Maiden Plate
race.comment: ALL THE MOVES (1) stepped up to 2000m at Wangaratta last time and got into third, beaten 2.5 lengths. He should be peaking now and is open to further improvement being relatively lightly raced. He should be very hard to hold out. CONALTRI (2) has had a few chances but put in a better effort last time at Great Western when narrowly edged out. This isn't a whole lot harder and he can figure with a follow-up effort. SAXON BLOOD (4) did beat BOY FROM OZ home when they met, he was solid again last time at Moe. Can roll forward and give a sight. HARRY CAVIAR (3) should be ready for a rise in trip fourth up and has claims despite a tricky draw.
